values: Hello, everybody; welcome to my journal. This is my family, except for my brand new son-in-law. http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v444/StarWatcher/ef95b9a0.jpg

I got this from StarWatcher. It turns out that --
My Peculiar Aristocratic Title is:
Her Eminence the Very Viscountess Cindyrama the Calm of Bismorton Shropcake
Get your Peculiar Aristocratic Title
I certainly am glad that I'm from such an... edible place!

Happy 2006 Everyone!
I just saw a photo of myself five years ago and I don't even remember that happy, active person.  So many difficulties have changed me to an entirely different person.  How do I get back to where I was?  How does a person undo so much damage?  It's not just the years - I know it has to be the events and their combined unhappiness.  In five years I feel as if I have aged fifty.  I even see things differently.  I just don't know my way back.  Anybody got any practical (or even impractical) ideas for reversing the process of depression?
I'm really needing some kind of help.
My friend StarWatcher made me do this.  Let's see how much I use it.
